    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="536"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d536">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.12155/459: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Ciudad Judrez</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Blocker</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-10T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 10, 1930—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Please deliver following message to Boundary Commissioner Lawson: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Reference telegram No. 208, September 9, 4 p.m. from American Embassy,
                            Mexico City, to Department copy of which is stated to have been sent to
                            you by airmail. Reference also to draft Minute referred to in
                            telegram.</p>
                        <p>When you have received draft Minute please consult with Mexican
                            Commissioner Serrano and send your observations thereon to the
                            Department.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
